**Features:** admin login, dashboard with stats (total/active/inactive/admin counts) and user list, create/edit/deactivate/reactivate accounts, data persisted in SQLite.

## How the mandatory security requirements are met

- **SQL injection** ‚Äî all queries use `?` parameter binding (`db.py`); no string-built SQL.
- **Password hashing** ‚Äî bcrypt, cost 12, per-password salt (`security.py`).
- **XSS** ‚Äî Jinja2 context-aware autoescaping + strict CSP (`default-src 'none'`, no inline/remote scripts); input validated via WTForms (username regex, email validator, length caps).
- **CSRF** ‚Äî Flask-WTF `CSRFProtect` enforces a token on *every* POST including login and logout.
- **Access control / IDOR** ‚Äî all dashboard routes require an authenticated active admin, re-checked from the DB each request; admins can't deactivate/demote themselves.
- **Session cookies** ‚Äî `HttpOnly`, `Secure` (default on), `SameSite=Lax`, 30-min lifetime; session cleared on login to prevent fixation.
- **Security headers** ‚Äî CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy, Permissions-Policy, HSTS (when HTTPS).
- **No leaked errors** ‚Äî `debug=False`, custom error pages, exceptions logged server-side only.
- **No hardcoded secrets** ‚Äî `SECRET_KEY` and all config read from environment / `.env`.

